  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting Niger National Vaccination Campaign through Capacity-Building, Logistical and Sensitization Support in the Agadez Region</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The intervention will contribute to tackling the risk of COVID-19 spread in Niger through targeted support to vaccinate vulnerable groups of migrants in the region of Agadez. In the framework of the upcoming vaccination campaign, which prioritizes migrants, and refugees due to the increased epidemiological risk raised by mobility, IOM Niger will support the national response by (1) Supporting the capacity of health providers and staff in the region of Agadez (2) Supporting the logistics required by vaccination delivery and implementation (3) and supporting sensitization activities in Agadez region. Operations will result in delivering stronger health response across the region, benefitting to an estimated 20,000 direct beneficiaries in Agadez and contributing to the development of logistical solutions useful to the overall COVID-19 response. Activities will positively impact a vulnerable social segment, migrants and returnees being at risk of being stigmatized as vectors of COVID19 while already often suffering traumatic or health issues.</narrative>
  </description>
